songs.title: Hollywood
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
One day, my hoops will be made of diamonds
My knuckles made of real gold
I'll spend my days getting high with all my friends
In the glamorous and green old part of Hollywood

[Pre-Chorus]
Sun will rise, I'm a supernova
Body electric and I dance like Morrison
When the night begins, baby comes alive again

[Chorus]
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
I'm alive again
I'm alive again

[Verse 2]
One day, I'll drive in a gold Mercedes Benz
Singing opera on Bel Air Road
Hair to my ass will be flying in the wind
Shootin' heroin and speedballs

[Pre-Chorus]
See the sea, I'm a supernova
I walk on water and I dance like Joplin
When the sun descends, I dive into the waves again

[Chorus]
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
I'm alive again
I'm alive again

[Bridge]
Oh-oh, oh-oh, c-can you see me?
Whoa-oh, my heart beating fast
I can feel it chasing in the speed-lights
I was built to last
Whoa-oh, c-can you feel that?
Ah-ah, ah-ah, my heart shakin' fast
I can feel that you're the one for me
You'll be my first, and you'll be my last

[Chorus]
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
In Hollywood
I'm alive again
I'm alive again

[Outro]
I'm alive again
I'm alive again
